    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>Hi there, Maria.  Yep, you could most certainly make the tart shells ahead of time.  You could bake them and then freeze them, and then let them thaw fully before filling them with the lemon mixture. I can&#8217;t remember for certain, but the finished tarts might even last a day or two with no adverse effects on their quality.  Give them a test run and see what you think! Good luck to you, and congratulations to your brother.</p>
    </div>

